I'm already quite used to living here.

5
00:01:44,150 --> 00:01:46,690
And just like you said,

6
00:01:47,350 --> 00:01:48,690
it's all your people out there.

7
00:01:48,710 --> 00:01:49,570
I told you,

8
00:01:50,590 --> 00:01:51,850
it's safer at my place.

9
00:01:55,710 --> 00:01:57,020
Besides,

10
00:01:57,040 --> 00:01:59,690
as the deputy director
of the Cryptography Institute,

11
00:02:00,150 --> 00:02:02,410
you should set an example for others.

12
00:02:02,950 --> 00:02:03,490
Am I right?

13
00:02:07,710 --> 00:02:09,060
You're thoughtful, Director Liang.

14
00:02:09,310 --> 00:02:11,290
Then I'll trouble you with this.

15
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:13,010
Tomorrow at noon,

16
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:14,890
we'll be waiting on time.

17
00:02:17,030 --> 00:02:17,690
I'll take my leave.

18
00:02:42,150 --> 00:02:42,980
Gu Yangshan.

19
00:02:44,560 --> 00:02:46,130
Who is Liang Jingyuan

20
00:02:46,150 --> 00:02:47,130
exactly?

21
00:02:49,710 --> 00:02:51,410
He used to work at the Suzhou Bureau,

22
00:02:52,150 --> 00:02:53,820
but he often has contact
with the Shanghai Bureau.

23
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:56,410
I suspect he must have defected.

24
00:02:57,280 --> 00:02:59,820
Looks like the Shanghai Bureau
has all gone rogue.

25
00:03:00,030 --> 00:03:01,290
Fortunately, he hasn't seen me before.

26
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:08,570
Gu Yangshan.

27
00:03:09,710 --> 00:03:11,220
Now your Shanghai Bureau

28
00:03:11,240 --> 00:03:11,820
has been taken down.

29
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:13,850
Doesn't that mean
you're the only one left?

30
00:03:13,870 --> 00:03:14,980
What do you plan to do?

31
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:16,540
I still think I should find a way

32
00:03:16,560 --> 00:03:18,100
to get you out as soon as possible.

33
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:20,980
I'll go check the back.

34
00:03:32,190 --> 00:03:33,380
No one's here. Hurry.

35
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:34,170
I'm not going.

36
00:03:35,590 --> 00:03:36,130
What did you say?

37
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:37,820
I said I'm not going.

38
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:41,690
This is our land, our home.

39
00:03:41,710 --> 00:03:42,690
Why should we

40
00:03:42,710 --> 00:03:44,380
be chased everywhere by the Japanese?

41
00:03:44,560 --> 00:03:46,610
Back then I fled
from the Northeast to Baimahu,

42
00:03:46,630 --> 00:03:48,610
then from Baimahu to Shanghai.

43
00:03:48,630 --> 00:03:49,730
Haven't I run far enough?

44
00:03:49,750 --> 00:03:50,500
And what happened?

45
00:03:51,120 --> 00:03:52,730
Now the streets
are still full of Japanese.

46
00:03:52,750 --> 00:03:53,610
I don't agree!

47
00:03:54,750 --> 00:03:56,060
Aren't you being unreasonable?

48
00:03:56,520 --> 00:03:57,610
Acting on impulse like this,

49
00:03:57,630 --> 00:03:58,610
do you have a death wish?

50
00:03:58,630 --> 00:03:59,500
I'm not being unreasonable.

51
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:00,890
Everything I said is from the heart.

52
00:04:00,910 --> 00:04:02,380
And you've also said before

53
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:03,820
that if everyone runs away,

54
00:04:04,310 --> 00:04:05,780
then we won't be far
from losing our country.

55
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:08,500
Now you're the only one left
in the Shanghai Bureau.

56
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:09,610
Without me,

57
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:10,340
it's simply impossible

58
00:04:10,360 --> 00:04:11,540
to complete the Sword Thrust Operation.

59
00:04:12,960 --> 00:04:14,380
If I run now,

60
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:16,610
wouldn't all the effort
you've put into me

61
00:04:16,630 --> 00:04:17,780
be wasted?

62
00:04:17,800 --> 00:04:19,780
Joseph Lee's code
has already been replaced.

63
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:21,290
And you personally killed Takeda.

64
00:04:21,310 --> 00:04:22,410
You've already done enough.

65
00:04:22,430 --> 00:04:23,540
I'm very grateful to you.

66
00:04:24,750 --> 00:04:25,730
Neither of us knows

67
00:04:25,750 --> 00:04:26,980
what exactly is happening

68
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,490
inside the Cryptography Institute.

69
00:04:28,870 --> 00:04:31,290
Now Liang Jingyuan is not only
making you deputy director,

70
00:04:31,310 --> 00:04:33,100
he's also moving you into Sanyangli.

71
00:04:34,310 --> 00:04:36,100
Do you know what that means?

72
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:37,980
It means every day
you'll be dealing with cipher experts

73
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,850
and codebreaking specialists.

74
00:04:41,480 --> 00:04:42,730
You're not a soldier, nor an agent.

75
00:04:43,870 --> 00:04:45,100
But Liang Jingyuan is different.

76
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:47,980
He is extremely suspicious.

77
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:49,980
If he could notice
your accent was off today,

78
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:51,850
tomorrow he would definitely
find more issues

79
00:04:51,870 --> 00:04:53,730
on Joseph Lee that shouldn't exist.

80
00:04:53,750 --> 00:04:54,980
Once there's any slip-up,

81
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:56,730
there's no way we could salvage it.

82
00:04:57,120 --> 00:04:58,980
You know how quick I can learn.

83
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:00,980
And my performance before wasn't bad.

84
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:03,100
You can teach me
whatever I don't understand.

85
00:05:03,750 --> 00:05:06,290
I won't. You must leave today.

86
00:05:31,630 --> 00:05:32,850
The day Uncle Gu sacrificed himself,

87
00:05:35,190 --> 00:05:36,660
it wasn't just you who felt sorrow.

88
00:05:39,430 --> 00:05:40,410
I stayed alone,

89
00:05:42,310 --> 00:05:43,730
thinking in my room all night.

90
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:49,850
Lead by example.

91
00:05:50,750 --> 00:05:51,540
These three words

92
00:05:52,120 --> 00:05:53,170
are your family motto.

93
00:05:54,750 --> 00:05:57,290
Uncle Gu, and even your younger sister

94
00:05:58,310 --> 00:06:00,170
could give away their own lives

95
00:06:00,750 --> 00:06:02,660
to defend these three words.

96
00:06:05,120 --> 00:06:06,410
But shouldn't these three words

97
00:06:08,630 --> 00:06:09,410
also be the responsibility

98
00:06:09,430 --> 00:06:11,170
that we ordinary people

99
00:06:12,630 --> 00:06:13,980
should carry on our shoulders?

100
00:06:28,750 --> 00:06:29,540
Ding Yi.

101
00:06:31,430 --> 00:06:33,050
We've been through so much together.

102
00:06:35,680 --> 00:06:36,980
In my heart,

103
00:06:38,950 --> 00:06:40,490
you're a friend
I can trust with my life.

104
00:06:43,190 --> 00:06:45,850
Actually, I have only one goal for you.

105
00:06:47,310 --> 00:06:48,730
It's to keep you safe.

106
00:06:51,750 --> 00:06:53,410
But after all you just said,

107
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:54,730
I understand too

108
00:06:55,950 --> 00:06:57,930
that you're no longer
what you used to be.

109
00:07:00,430 --> 00:07:01,850
But if you stay,

110
00:07:04,190 --> 00:07:05,730
we will be facing

111
00:07:05,750 --> 00:07:07,410
unprecedented difficulties.

112
00:07:10,630 --> 00:07:12,050
Have you really thought this through?

113
00:07:13,630 --> 00:07:14,580
Do you really want to do this?

114
00:07:23,430 --> 00:07:24,170
I'm an actor.

115
00:07:27,720 --> 00:07:29,490
This is my most desired role.

116
00:07:31,190 --> 00:07:32,980
As long as you can help set my stage,

117
00:07:34,920 --> 00:07:38,900
I'll definitely be able
to play this part well.

118
00:07:50,120 --> 00:07:50,660
Alright.

119
00:07:52,870 --> 00:07:54,140
We'll let those spectators

120
00:07:55,270 --> 00:07:55,850
wait and see.

